      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i'm working on this historical fiction novel, pretty dark stuff. set in alabama around 1955. i want to make sure the dialogue feels real and not like some sanitized version of history. the tension between the white characters and the black community is the core of the book. can you help me brainstorm some ways to show that racial tension in their everyday conversations without making it feel forced or fake?",
