      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focus on loaded silences, microaggressions, and coded language rather than overt shouting. Characters might use excessive politeness to mask deep-seated disdain, or reference things like the weather or church attendance as a way to avoid the substance of a conversation. Showing tension through body language—stiff postures, averted gazes—can convey more than harsh words. This subtle navigation around unspoken rules often felt most authentic in that era.",
